Step 1. Calculate ROE using the average owner's equity.  
• Beginning Owner’s Equity (2023-12-31) = 13,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner’s Equity (2024-01-29) = 14,163,543.07  
• Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 14,163,543.07) / 2 = 13,581,771.535  
• Net Profit (from the income statement) = 1,163,543.07  
• ROE = Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity = 1,163,543.07 / 13,581,771.535 ≈ 0.08567, or 8.57%

Step 2. Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• Total Assets (2024-01-29) = 15,288,131.32  
• Total Owner’s Equity (2024-01-29) = 14,163,543.07  
• Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Owner’s Equity = 15,288,131.32 – 14,163,543.07 = 1,124,588.25  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 1,124,588.25 / 15,288,131.32 ≈ 0.07356, or about 0.07

Step 3. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit (from income statement) = 2,741,764.34  
• Total Revenue (from income statement) = 5,991,764.34  
• Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue = 2,741,764.34 / 5,991,764.34 ≈ 0.4576, or 45.76%

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "8.57%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.07",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "45.76%"
  }
}
